## Deployment Environment

### AWS EC2 Deployment

The prototype is deployed on Amazon Web Services (AWS) using an EC2 virtual machine.

#### Instance Details

| Component        | Value                   |
| ---------------- | ----------------------- |
| Cloud Provider   | AWS                     |
| Service          | EC2                     |
| Operating System | Ubuntu Server 24.04 LTS |
| Instance Type    | t3.micro                |
| Architecture     | x86_64                  |
| Public Access    | HTTP                    |
| Runtime          | Python 3.14             |
| Web Server       | Uvicorn                 |
| Process Manager  | Systemd                 |

---

### Application Architecture

```text
User Browser
      │
      ▼
FastAPI Web Application
      │
      ├── Application Builder
      ├── OCR Processing
      ├── PDF Processing
      ├── Validation Engine
      └── Batch Processing
               │
               ▼
       Validation Results
```

---

### Deployment Objectives

The deployment environment was intentionally designed to:

* Minimize operational cost
* Require no external cloud AI services
* Run entirely within the server boundary
* Demonstrate suitability for restricted government environments
* Avoid outbound dependencies that could be blocked by agency firewalls

This approach aligns with stakeholder concerns regarding security restrictions and network controls.

---

### Local Processing Design

All processing occurs locally on the EC2 instance.

No label images, forms, or OCR data are transmitted to third-party services.

Processing components include:

* Tesseract OCR
* PyMuPDF
* FastAPI
* Validation Engine

Benefits:

* Reduced latency
* No external API costs
* No internet dependency
* Improved privacy
* Easier compliance review

---

### Performance Considerations

One of the key stakeholder requirements was response time.

A previous pilot reportedly required 30–40 seconds per label, leading users to abandon the system.

This prototype was designed with the following goals:

| Operation               | Target                            |
| ----------------------- | --------------------------------- |
| Single Image Validation | < 5 seconds                       |
| Front + Back Label Set  | < 10 seconds                      |
| PDF Processing          | < 10 seconds                      |
| Batch Validation        | Scales linearly by document count |

Performance depends primarily on:

* Image resolution
* OCR complexity
* PDF size
* Number of uploaded documents

